+## Web UI Extension Points
+
+### Navigation Targets
+
+The web UI exposes four named navigation zones where plugins can inject routes:
+
+```
+┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│  ┌──────┐  TOP TOOLBAR                           │
+│  │  ●   │  [PluginBtn] [PluginBtn2]              │
+│  ├──────┴───────────────────────────────────────┤ │
+│  │ SIDEBAR        │  MAIN CONTENT AREA          │ │
+│  │                │                             │ │
+│  │  Chat          │  ┌─────────────────────┐    │ │
+│  │  Repos         │  │                     │    │ │
+│  │  Issues  ◀──   │  │  Plugin Page        │    │ │
+│  │  Agents        │  │  Content            │    │ │
+│  │  ─────────     │  │                     │    │ │
+│  │  My Plugin     │  └─────────────────────┘    │ │
+│  │                │                             │ │
+│  ├────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┤ │
+│  │  SETTINGS: [Profile] [Plugin Settings]       │ │
+│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │
+│                                                    │
+│  DROPDOWN: [Account] [Logout] [Plugin Action]     │
+└────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+### Route Registration
+
+Plugin routes are contributed via `RouteContribution` and registered with TanStack Router. The web app reads `getPluginRoutes()` from the `PluginRegistry` and dynamically adds them to the router configuration.
+
+### Paint System
+
+Paints allow plugins to inject React components at specific DOM targets:
+
+```typescript
+// Example: Plugin wants to add a badge after the PR title
+const paint: PaintContribution = {
+  id: "my-pr-quality-badge",
+  target: "pr-title",
+  position: "after",
+  component: "QualityBadge",
+};
+```
+
+The web app reads `getPluginPaints()` and renders paints via a `<PaintSlot target="...">` component that iterates registered paints, sorted by position order.
+
+### Custom Routes
+
+Plugins can contribute full-page routes with their own React components. Components are referenced by string identifier and resolved through a component registry that plugins populate during activation.
+
+### UI Data Flow
+
+```
+Octokit REST API
+      │
+      ▼
+GitHubClient (Effect error wrapping)
+      │
+      ▼
+Service Layer (IssuesService, PullRequestsService, etc.)
+  Returns Effect<DomainType, GitHubError>
+      │
+      ▼
+Server WebSocket Route (wsServer.ts)
+  Wraps Effect in request/response pattern
+      │
+      ▼
+WebSocket Push (channel: orchestration.domainEvent)
+      │
+      ▼
+React Client (lib/ actions + TanStack Router loaders)
+  Effect.runPromise on WebSocket responses
+      │
+      ▼
+UI Components (React + Tailwind + shadcn/ui)
+```
+
