+### C. T3 Code Interfaces Extended by OmniCode
+
+| T3 Code Interface | Role | OmniCode Extension |
+|-------------------|------|-------------------|
+| `SourceControlProviderShape` | Provider abstraction (gh CLI-based) | `@omnicode/github` services add Octokit-based GitHub provider |
+| `SourceControlProviderRegistry` | Dispatches providers by remote URL | Plugin `ProviderContribution` adds new providers dynamically |
+| `VcsDriver` | Git/Jujutsu VCS abstraction | Unchanged — worktree operations use VcsDriver |
+| `SourceControlProviderKind` | Provider kind enum (`github`, `gitlab`, etc.) | Extended by plugins via `ProviderType` (`"gitea"`, `"custom"`) |
+| `ChangeRequest` | PR/MR data structure | Used by `PullRequestsService` to correlate Octokit data |
+
+### D. Glossary
+
+| Term | Definition |
+|------|-----------|
+| **Plugin** | A third-party extension packaged as a module with a manifest |
+| **Agent** | An AI agent implementing the `Agent` base class for automated tasks |
+| **Provider** | A Git hosting backend (GitHub, GitLab, etc.) |
+| **Paint** | A UI decoration that injects content at named DOM targets |
+| **Hook** | A plugin lifecycle event (e.g., `pr:created`, `agent:before_run`) |
+| **Extension Point** | A named location in the UI or system where plugins can contribute |
+| **Worktree** | A linked Git working directory for parallel branch development |
+| **Octokit** | The official GitHub REST API client library for JavaScript |
+| **Effect** | The TypeScript library for typed, composable, resource-safe programming |
